WorkItem.Description:
I get the following error.  This seems like a bug in the DataGrid...
 
InvalidOperationException: A TwoWay or OneWayToSource binding cannot work on the read-only property 'Bar' of type 'Foo'
 
Here is the source...
 
    internal class Foo
    {
        public string Bar
        {
            get { return "Baz"; }
        }
    }
 
 
...and the OnInitialized in the window...
 
 
    protected override void OnInitialized(EventArgs e)
    {
        base.OnInitialized(e);
 
        var c = new ObservableCollection<Foo>();
        c.Add(new Foo());
        c.Add(new Foo());
        c.Add(new Foo());
        dgrEnums.ItemsSource = c;
    }
 
...and the XAML snippet...
 
    <dg:DataGrid x:Name="dgrEnums" 
                 HeadersVisibility="Column"
                 AutoGenerateColumns="False">
        <dg:DataGrid.Columns>
            <dg:DataGridTextColumn Binding="{Binding Path=Bar, Mode=OneWay}" Header="Enumeration" />
        </dg:DataGrid.Columns>
    </dg:DataGrid>
 
I'm setting the mode to OneWay.  However, it still fails saying that TwoWay and OneWayToSource cannot be used with readonly properties.
 
 
Also, note that I MUST put the HeadersVisibility="Column" attribute.  If I leave it at the default, "All", I get a row header on the column row, but *not* on the item rows.  So, the cells don't line up with the column headers.
 
Is there a list of known problems available for the DataGrid control?
 
 
Thanks,
Gary
